cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computing finite difference Groebner bases of polynomial ideals. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for computing finite difference Groebner bases. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper deals with decision criteria for certain properties of polynomial ideals. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a possible category as the paper involves reducing complicated properties to elementary properties.
